               <p>JOHN HUNT. I live in White Hart-yard, Drury-lane, and bawk provisions about. On the 5th of September, about half-past four o'clock in the afternoon, I left my house - I had been with some friends, and got tipsy; coming home my wife began to blow me up, and I ran away from her - I do not know where I went, and I found myself in Falcon-court, Fleet-street, about half-past five in the morning - I was stripped naked, all but my stockings and shirt; I lost 7s. 9d. in money.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-332-person2396">
                  RICHARD 
                  BRODRICK
               <interp inst="t18310908-332-person2396" type="surname" value="BRODRICK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-332-person2396" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-332-person2396" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Policeman. I took the prisoner into custody about twenty minutes to two o'clock in the morning, in Vere-street, Clare-market, with a bundle under his arm - I asked what he had; he said a pair of trousers and shoes, which I found in the bundle; he had got the coat on his back, and the waistcoat in his own coat pocket - he did not say how he came by it; the prosecutor saw the clothes when he was sober, and identified them.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I never saw the man before - I was returning from Greenwich, and saw these things by the Olympic Theatre.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310908-332-verdict1709" type="verdictDescription">
